Package com.kamarbaraka.practice

Class Employee

java.lang.Object
com.kamarbaraka.practice.Employee
public class Employee extends Object
a simple class to store employee information. it takes the employee name, initial salary and date of employment and stores it. it has methods: getName(), getSalary(), getHireDate() that returns the name, the salary and the date of hire respectively. It also has methods raiseSalary() that raises the salary of the particular employee by a percentage,saves it and returns the resultant value. Method info() returns an array that contains. the information of the particular employee and toString() that returns a string representation of the object
Version:
2.0
Author:
kamar baraka
